  "description": "<ul><li><p><strong>Well Established Company</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Basic $3000 - $3500 + AWS + Variable Bonus</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Excellent Welfare and Benefits + Career progression</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Working location: East</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Working hours: Monday to Friday (9am to 6pm)</strong><br /></p></li></ul><p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Prepare full of accounts</p></li><li><p>Perform bank reconciliation, track payments</p></li><li><p>Support audit and tax matters</p></li><li><p>Maintain accurate books of accounts and financial records</p></li><li><p>Prepare and process invoices, payments, and receipts</p></li><li><p>Perform other assigned duties<br /></p></li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Possess minimum Diploma in Accountancy, LCCI, CAT, or equivalent with minimum 2 years of relevant accounting experience<br /></p></li></ul><p>Candidates are encouraged to apply this position via <strong>Apply Now </strong>button with the following information in the resume<br /></p><ul><li><p>Work experiences and job responsibilities</p></li><li><p>Current and Expected salary</p></li><li><p>Reason for leaving</p></li><li><p>Date of availability</p></li><li><p>Education background<br /></p></li></ul><p>We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.<br /></p><p>LIONG ZHAO GUAN (R22107632)</p><p>EA Recruitment Pte Ltd</p><p>EA License No: 21C0492</p>",
